#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:2
msgid "Understanding Meson"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:4
msgid ""
"Building NumPy relies on the following tools, which can be considered part "
"of the build system:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:7
msgid ""
"``meson``: the Meson build system, installable as a pure Python package from "
"PyPI or conda-forge"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:9
msgid ""
"``ninja``: the build tool invoked by Meson to do the actual building (e.g. "
"invoking compilers). Installable also from PyPI (on all common platforms) or "
"conda-forge."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:12
msgid ""
"``pkg-config``: the tool used for discovering dependencies (in particular "
"BLAS/LAPACK). Available on conda-forge (and Homebrew, Chocolatey, and Linux "
"package managers), but not packaged on PyPI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:15
msgid ""
"``meson-python``: the Python build backend (i.e., the thing that gets "
"invoked via a hook in ``pyproject.toml`` by a build frontend like ``pip`` or "
"``pypa/build``). This is a thin layer on top of Meson, with as main roles "
"(a) interface with build frontends, and (b) produce sdists and wheels with "
"valid file names and metadata."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:23
msgid ""
"As of Dec'23, NumPy vendors a custom version of Meson, which is needed for "
"SIMD and BLAS/LAPACK features that are not yet available in upstream Meson. "
"Hence, using the ``meson`` executable directly is not possible. Instead, "
"wherever instructions say ``meson xxx``, use ``python vendored-meson/meson/"
"meson.py xxx`` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:29
msgid "Building with Meson happens in stages:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:31
msgid ""
"A configure stage (``meson setup``) to detect compilers, dependencies and "
"build options, and create the build directory and ``build.ninja`` file,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:33
msgid ""
"A compile stage (``meson compile`` or ``ninja``), where the extension "
"modules that are part of a built NumPy package get compiled,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:35
msgid ""
"An install stage (``meson install``) to install the installable files from "
"the source and build directories to the target install directory,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:38
msgid ""
"Meson has a good build dependency tracking system, so invoking a build for a "
"second time will rebuild only targets for which any sources or dependencies "
"have changed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:44
msgid "To learn more about Meson"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:46
msgid ""
"Meson has `very good documentation <https://mesonbuild.com/>`__; it pays off "
"to read it, and is often the best source of answers for \"how to do X\". "
"Furthermore, an extensive pdf book on Meson can be obtained for free at "
"https://nibblestew.blogspot.com/2021/12/this-year-receive-gift-of-free-meson."
"html"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:51
msgid ""
"To learn more about the design principles Meson uses, the recent talks "
"linked from `mesonbuild.com/Videos <https://mesonbuild.com/Videos.html>`__ "
"are also a good resource."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:57
msgid "Explanation of build stages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:59
msgid ""
"*This is for teaching purposes only; there should be no need to execute "
"these stages separately!*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:62
msgid ""
"Assume we're starting from a clean repo and a fully set up conda "
"environment::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:64
msgid ""
"git clone git@github.com:numpy/numpy.git\n"
"git submodule update --init\n"
"mamba env create -f environment.yml\n"
"mamba activate numpy-dev"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:69
msgid ""
"To now run the configure stage of the build and instruct Meson to put the "
"build artifacts in ``build/`` and a local install under ``build-install/`` "
"relative to the root of the repo, do::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:73
msgid "meson setup build --prefix=$PWD/build-install"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:75
msgid "To then run the compile stage of the build, do::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:77
msgid "ninja -C build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:79
msgid ""
"In the command above, ``-C`` is followed by the name of the build directory. "
"You can have multiple build directories at the same time. Meson is fully out-"
"of-place, so those builds will not interfere with each other. You can for "
"example have a GCC build, a Clang build and a debug build in different "
"directories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:85
msgid ""
"To then install NumPy into the prefix (``build-install/`` here, but note "
"that that's just an arbitrary name we picked here)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:88
msgid "meson install -C build"
msgstr "meson install -C build"

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:90
msgid ""
"It will then install to ``build-install/lib/python3.12/site-packages/"
"numpy``, which is not on your Python path, so to add it do (*again, this is "
"for learning purposes, using ``PYTHONPATH`` explicitly is typically not the "
"best idea*)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:94
msgid "export PYTHONPATH=$PWD/build-install/lib/python3.12/site-packages/"
msgstr "export PYTHONPATH=$PWD/build-install/lib/python3.12/site-packages/"

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:96
msgid ""
"Now we should be able to import ``numpy`` and run the tests. Remembering "
"that we need to move out of the root of the repo to ensure we pick up the "
"package and not the local ``numpy/`` source directory::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:100
msgid ""
"cd doc\n"
"python -c \"import numpy as np; np.test()\""
msgstr ""
"cd doc\n"
"python -c \"import numpy as np; np.test()\""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:103
msgid ""
"The above runs the \"fast\" numpy test suite. Other ways of running the "
"tests should also work, for example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:106
msgid "pytest --pyargs numpy"
msgstr "pytest --pyargs numpy"

#: ../../../building/understanding_meson.rst:108
msgid ""
"The full test suite should pass, without any build warnings on Linux (with "
"the GCC version for which ``-Werror`` is enforced in CI at least) and with "
"at most a moderate amount of warnings on other platforms."
msgstr ""
